The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Renovation of Eden
                                                   Renovation of Eden
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) took its first step towards the proposed renovation of the Eden Gardens, ahead of the 2011 World Cup, as two companies presented their proposals in presence of the working committee members on Thursday.         
	Burt Hill, an American company, in association with VMS of Ahmedabad and HOK of Singapore in collaboration with the Kolkata Knight Riders, made the presentations.         
	The CAB has made extensive plans for an overall makeover of the stadium and according to president Jagmohan Dalmiya, a final decision on the matter will be taken within a week.                                                                                                                       
